A_557 - It is important to remember that your lifestyle must be aligned based on the color of your skin: if you have dark skin and stay indoors too much or do an office job without taking other precautions, you will tend to start to feel very ill. Likewise, if you have very light skin but have chosen to do a job in the sun, your health may similarly be affected. To produce vitamin D, the skin must receive a quantity of sun which depends not only on the color of the skin but also on the latitude. The use of sun lamps or sun creams to vary the amount of of sunlight received by the skin is a system that still has costs, time spent dealing with it and perhaps even contraindications that we don't know about in the medium-long term...